This paper deals with collision simulations in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) and information theory (IT). The paper also proposes a simulation technique that can be applied to various cyclic protocols, which falls under the category of systems and control (SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of current simulation methods, which could be considered as a topic related to cryptography and security (CR) or performance analysis (PF).
